cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with computer vision and graphics, specifically in the area of pose estimation and image synthesis. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The use of deep generative models and neural synthesis also suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The paper also involves training the pipeline end-to-end, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a dense pose estimation system and the focus on image synthesis suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of adversarial and perceptual losses suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
